from dataclasses import dataclass

@dataclass
class Triple:
    subject: str
    predicate: str
    object: str

# EVOLVE-BLOCK-START

def predict(triples: list[Triple]) -> str:
    rules = {
        "cityServed": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} serves the city of {obj}.",
        "country": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} is located in {obj}.",
        "capital": lambda sub, obj: f"The capital of {sub} is {obj}.",
        "elevationAboveTheSeaLevel": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} has an elevation of {obj} meters above sea level.",
        "location": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} is located in {obj}.",
        "operatingOrganisation": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} is operated by {obj}.",
        "runwayLength": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} has a runway length of {obj} meters.",
        "runwayName": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} has a runway named {obj}.",
        "isPartOf": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} is part of {obj}.",
        "1stRunwayLengthFeet": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} has a first runway length of {obj} feet.",
        "1stRunwaySurfaceType": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} has a first runway surface type of {obj}.",
        "3rdRunwayLengthFeet": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} has a third runway length of {obj} feet.",
        "icaoLocationIdentifier": lambda sub, obj: f"The ICAO location identifier for {sub} is {obj}.",
        "locationIdentifier": lambda sub, obj: f"The location identifier for {sub} is {obj}.",
        "elevationAboveTheSeaLevelInFeet": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} is {obj} feet above sea level.",
        "iataLocationIdentifier": lambda sub, obj: f"The IATA location identifier for {sub} is {obj}.",
        "nativeName": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} is also known as {obj}.",
        "leaderParty": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} is led by the {obj}.",
        "language": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} speaks {obj}.",
        "owner": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} is owned by {obj}.",
        "1stRunwayLengthMetre": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} has a first runway length of {obj} metres.",
        "4thRunwaySurfaceType": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} has a fourth runway surface type of {obj}.",
        "largestCity": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub}'s largest city is {obj}.",
        "4thRunwayLengthFeet": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} has a fourth runway length of {obj} feet.",
        "elevationAboveTheSeaLevelInMetres": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} is {obj} metres above sea level.",
        "administrativeArrondissement": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} is in the {obj}.",
        "mayor": lambda sub, obj: f"The mayor of {sub} is {obj}.",
        "2ndRunwaySurfaceType": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} has a second runway surface type of {obj}.",
        "3rdRunwaySurfaceType": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} has a third runway surface type of {obj}.",
        "runwaySurfaceType": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} has a runway surface type of {obj}.",
        "officialLanguage": lambda sub, obj: f"The official language of {sub} is {obj}.",
        "hubAirport": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub}'s hub airport is {obj}.",
        "aircraftFighter": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} uses {obj} as a fighter aircraft.",
        "attackAircraft": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} uses {obj} as an attack aircraft.",
        "countySeat": lambda sub, obj: f"The county seat of {sub} is {obj}.",
        "foundingYear": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} was founded in {obj}.",
        "ceremonialCounty": lambda sub, obj: f"{sub} is in the ceremonial county of {obj}.",
    }

    sentence = ""
    for triple in triples:
        if triple.predicate in rules:
            sentence += rules[triple.predicate](triple.subject, triple.object) + " "

    return sentence
